
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
exkatampi.f90: Exciton energy Kataura plot
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Note:

- Now exkatampi.f90 does not use libjiang.
- When you calculate E77S and E33M, diameter range is between 1.0nm and 3.0nm.
- the calculation time for all (from E11S to E66S and from E11M to E33M)
  is about half or one day by using 24 CPUs in TUBE. Diameter range is
  between 0.7nm and 3.0nm.

usage:

0. Set parameters for compiling. see
   /home1/students/kentaro/for/mk/

1. Check parameters for calculation in exkatampi.f90 and exkataparameter.f90

2. Make directories "results" and "def". Calculation results will be written
   in these directories.
   "results" contains exciton Kataura plot (the name is qex-kat...dat)
   "def" contains dielectric function as a function of q vector
   (the name is def...dat)

3. Just type "make exkatampi" on TUBE or WIRE

4. Run the program by using  the script "exkatampi.sh".
   Before using this script, you must change the variable "MaxCPU" in this script.
   MaxCPU is used by "bsub". Such as

   $ bsub -n $MaxCPU ...

   Please select best number for your environment.
   In my case, MaxCPU is 10 on TUBE.
   So I use 20 CPUs because TUBE has 24 CPUs.

   After setting MaxCPU, run the script for example

   $ sh exkatampi.sh all all

   First argument denotes nanotube type. Here s0, s1, s2 and all mean
   metal, type I, type II and all types (metal, type I and type II),
   respectively.

   Second argument denote subband index 1...7 (MaxSubBand).

   Of course, You can calculate one subband:

   $ sh exkatampi.sh s1 3

   This command means calculating E33 of semiconducting Type I nanotubes.
